# Change Management Standards

- Work in small, reviewable slices.
- Keep one logical change per commit when possible.
- Do not include unrelated refactors with business logic changes.

## Commit and Handoff Notes

- Commit messages should explain intent and business impact.
- For risky changes, include a short rollback note.
- Add concise code comments where business rules are non-obvious.
- Prefer "why" comments over "what" comments.

## Definition of Done (per change)

- Behavior is verified with a quick test or smoke check.
- Access control and scope boundaries are preserved.
- Docs are updated when behavior or decisions change.
